tr.td: Title: Primary Care telehealth visit toc

1. Hospital acquired PNA (J18.9: Pneumonia, unspecified organism)
Hospital-acquired pneumonia on recent hospitalization. Treated with antibiotics. Feeling well today.
2. Anemia (D64.9: Anemia, unspecified)
Patient noted to be significantly iron deficient during hospitalization. Discontinued oral iron and given iron infusion during hospitalization. Saw hematology today. Will have follow-up in 5 weeks. Monitor for blood in the stool
3. Chronic kidney disease, stage 3b, GFR 33, Creatinine 1.84 Labs 2023-02-28 (N18.32: Chronic kidney disease, stage 3b)
Stage III chronic kidney disease. Recent exacerbation during hospitalization, likely due to hypotensive episodes. Most recent creatinine 1.5 before discharge. Recommend follow-up with nephrology. Has an appointment tomorrow.
4. Diabetes mellitus with Stage 3 CKD (chronic kidney disease) (E11.22: Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic chronic kidney disease)
Type 2 diabetes with chronic kidney disease. Wife states that fasting blood sugars between 180s to 200s. Currently on Farxiga 10 mg. He did not tolerate Ozempic injections. Recommend initiation of glimepiride 4 mg once a day before breakfast. Hold medication if fasting
Ordered:
glimepiride 4 mg oral tablet, 1 tabs, Oral, Daily, # 90 tabs, 0 Refill(s), Maintenance, Pharmacy: WALGREENS DRUG STORE #02832, 1 tab(s) Oral Daily, 176 cm, 2023-08-07 17:24:00 EST, Height/Length Measured, 72.4 kg, 2023-08-07 17:24:00 EST, Actual Weight
5. Hypertension (I10: Essential (primary) hypertension)
Blood pressure not well controlled. He seems to have labile readings. The wife states that after the hospital discharge she had blood pressures between 160s systolically. Yesterday it was 80 after medication. I have asked his wife to check his blood pressure 3 times a day and to give him half of a tablet of amlodipine with doxazosin and metoprolol in the morning and half a tablet of amlodipine and metoprolol in the evening. She is to make an appointment with the cardiologist.
